27/10/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Three leading formations -- the ruling Serb Democratic Party, the main opposition Union of Independent Social Democrats and the Party of Democratic Progress -- have backed the nomination of former BiH Ambassador to the United States Igor Davidovic to serve as BiH's chief negotiator with the EU. 
The leaders of the three parties met on Wednesday (26 October). 
The nominee must be decided on by 12 December. 
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 27/10/05; Fena, RTRS, PBS BiH - 26/10/05)
